savant.format
Class DataFormatter

java.lang.Object
  savant.format.DataFormatter
All Implemented Interfaces:
FormatProgressListener
public class DataFormatter
extends java.lang.Object
implements FormatProgressListener

Class to perform formatting of biological data files (FASTA, BED, etc.) into Savant's binary formats. Sometimes a separate index file is created. Occasionally, auxiliary files are created, such as coverage files for BAM maps.

DataFormatter

public DataFormatter(java.lang.String inPath,
                     java.lang.String outPath,
                     FileType fileType,
                     boolean isInputOneBased)
Establishes a data formatter which can be run by calling the format() function.

Parameters:
inPath - input file path
outPath - output file path (should not already exist)
fileType - type of the input file (e.g. interval, point, etc)
isInputOneBased - whether or not the file is one-based (i.e. annotation of 10 refers to the 10th position in the genome, not the 9th as in zero-based scheme)
